# |||||||| Style Guide

## Scope and Purpose

Use this guide as a set of standards for writing:
- Posts
- Articles
- Work instructions
- Standard operating procedures

for ||||||||.

The goal of this document is to help technical writers and subject matter experts (SMEs) produce content that is:

- Clear and concise
- Written in plain language
- User-friendly
- Easily accessible
- Tailored to specific reader tasks
- Visually appealing

---

## Reader Engagement

### Identify Your Audience

- Identify who will use the document.
- Write in a way that helps the reader complete tasks quickly, efficiently, and effectively.

### Organize Material Logically

- Organize procedures by relevance.
- Structure content using:
  - What
  - Why
  - When
  - How
- Use nouns instead of pronouns where clarity is needed:
  - Use “The Engineer” instead of “They”
- Address users directly when appropriate.

### Pronoun Reference

| Perspective     | Subjective     | Objective     | Possessive            |
|-----------------|----------------|----------------|------------------------|
| First Person    | I, we          | Me, us         | My/mine, our/ours     |
| Second Person   | You            | You            | Your/yours            |
| Third Person    | He, she, it, they | Him, her, it, them | His/hers/its/their(s) |

